definitions.definition: A division into smaller pieces of something that has already been divided .
Such a piece that has been divided.
examples: Work on one subdivision at a time.

definitions.definition: A parcel of land that has been divided into lots .
A group of houses created by the same builder or in the same general area.
examples: They're putting in a new subdivision out past Black Ranch Road.

definitions.definition: A gated community located within a barangay .

main_definition: ( countable , uncountable ) A division into smaller pieces of something that has already been divided .
secondary_definitions: ( countable ) Such a piece that has been divided.
( countable ) A parcel of land that has been divided into lots .
( countable ) A group of houses created by the same builder or in the same general area.
( Philippines ) A gated community located within a barangay .
